                                <div id="seo-content-1-17" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="seo-content-heading-1-17">
                                    <div class="panel-body">
                                        <div class="editor-content">
                                            <p>With a Big Data Analytics certification, you will be able to make a major career shift. They are proof of competency and are accepted worldwide. As technology keeps changing every few months, getting a full-fledged degree is challenging. Certifications are an easy way to build the required talent. Here are a few benefits of enrolling in the Big Data Analytics certification course:</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>The technology is predicted to have great prospects in the future. As Big data is moving from the experimental phase to the real projects, there is a demand for Big Data Analytics professionals.</li>
                                                <li>With the attention currently given to Big Data Analytics, this has created a huge demand for talent to meet the ongoing demands. The gap in demand and supply has given a huge financial edge to the data professionals.</li>
                                                <li>When you get the Big data certification, you are starting your journey from a traditional IT job to a futuristic Data Analytics professional. Also, you can specialize in the number of subfields under Big Data Analytics accordingly.</li>
                                                <li>Getting the Big Data Analytics certification is only a small learning investment. You don’t have to take a break from your career and go to college. There are a number of courses available that you can choose from.</li>
                                                <li>Today, every sector is trying to leverage the power of big data and analytics. With the Big Data Analytics certification, you will have multiple job opportunities across different industries.</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="panel panel-default">
                                <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="seo-content-heading-1-18">
                                    <h4 class="panel-title"> <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent=".seo-content-accordion-1" href="#seo-content-1-18" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="seo-content-1-18">Are data science and Big Data Analytics one and the same?</a> </h4>
                                </div>
                                <div id="seo-content-1-18" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="seo-content-heading-1-18">
                                    <div class="panel-body">
                                        <div class="editor-content">
                                            <p>No, there is a huge difference between data science and Big Data Analytics.</p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><b>Concept</b>
                                                    <ul>
                                                        <li><b>Data Science -</b> Data Science encompasses everything related to data- from preparing to cleaning to analyzing the data, structured and unstructured. It combines mathematics, statistics and problem-solving.</li>
                                                        <li><b>Big Data Analytics -</b> It involves applying algorithmic or mechanical processes for deriving insights for complex business solutions. It combines inspection, transformation, cleansing and modelling data.</li>
                                                    </ul>
                                                </li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p></p>
                                            <ul></ul>
                                            <p></p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><b>Professionals</b>
                                                    <ul>
                                                        <li style=""><b>Data Science -</b> They perform exploratory analysis for obtaining insights from data. Different machine learning algorithms are used for identifying the occurrence of a particular event in the future. It focuses on identifying hidden patterns, unknown relations, and market trends.</li>
                                                        <li style=""><b>Big Data analytics -</b> They deal with large volumes of heterogeneous data that is captured from multiple sources and is arriving at a high velocity. As a Big Data Analytics professional, you will describe the structure and behaviour of big data solutions and deliver them using big data technologies like Hadoop and Spark, depending on the requirements.</li>
                                                    </ul>
                                                </li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p></p>
                                            <ul></ul>
                                            <p></p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><b>Required skill sets</b>
                                                    <ul>
                                                        <li><b>Data Science - </b>Excellent analytical skills, data management skills, mathematics, statistics, and programming skills. This includes understanding of C/C++, R, Java, Pearl, SAS, python, etc. You can use any of these for Data Science, depending on what you are comfortable with. Also, you must have technical skills associated with data mining, machine learning tools, unstructured data techniques, and data managing skills. Knowledge of database systems and essential business skills are a must.</li>
                                                        <li><b>Big Data Analytics - </b>Understanding of R, Python, statistics and mathematics skills, data wrangling skills, data visualization, communication skills, and machine learning skills.</li>
                                                    </ul>
                                                </li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="panel panel-default">
                                <div class="panel-heading" role="tab" id="seo-content-heading-1-19">
                                    <h4 class="panel-title"> <a class="collapsed" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent=".seo-content-accordion-1" href="#seo-content-1-19" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="seo-content-1-19">How to learn Big Data Analytics from scratch?</a> </h4>
